Auxton Computer Enterprises Incsaid it has entered into an agreement to provide cellularbusiness office services to a major non-wireline cellularcarrier in 12 major cellular markets throughout the U.S.    It said it has also reached agreement to determine theprocess needed to install its SOCRATES and LUCAS softwarepackages for a national communications carrier outside the U.S.    In addition it said it has agreed to start evaluating thefeasibility of installing its SOCRATES software to provide amajor national satellite paging company with billing servicesto subscribers traveling beyond the signal capacities of theirhome systems. Reuter&#3;